m Demo follow up, 10 Jul 2025"], "narrative": "Pain is extensively and consistently articulated: manual, disjointed UK-vs-US procurement and largely manual sourcing/contracting (Zycus Procurement System Demonstration, 16 May 2025); SQL-only, hard-to-build reporting ('frustration regarding the complexity of building reports', BH/Zycus Alignment, 23 May 2025); non-intuitive catalog UX hurting adoption; and manual invoice-to-PO discrepancy chasing causing delays ('The team faces challenges with manually chasing discrepancies between invoices and purchase orders, leading to delays in resolution', Zycus Procurement System Demo follow up, 10 Jul 2025). Pain owners: Andrew Duckworth/procurement for sourcing, Stuart Lamont for AP/invoicing, Faye Donnelly Renton for procurement management."}, "paper_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Zycus Procurement System Demo follow up, 10 Jul 2025", "Drop In Session - Nurseries Only, 2 Jun 2026", "SF Next_Step__c"], "narrative": "Catherine Wilson (Legal Counsel) attended the 10 Jul 2025 demo (benchmarking against DocuSign/SharePoint) and a dedicated Legal-only drop-in (3 Jun 2026, not recorded). DocuSign is confirmed as the intended e-signature platform ('Plan to integrate Zycus with DocuSign for contract signing workflow', Drop In Session - Nurseries Only, 2 Jun 2026). No MSA/SOW redline exchange is evidenced in the reviewed manifest, even though Next_Step__c targets redlining and signing within July immediately after vendor selection - this is the single biggest visibility gap on the deal right now."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Zycus Procurement System Demonstration, 16 May 2025", "Zycus Procurement System Demo follow up, 10 Jul 2025"], "narrative": "Joanne Urso, VP of Procurement (Decision Maker per contact role), named budget-relevant interest at the very first demo: 'Joanne Urso highlighted the interest in a globally scalable procurement system, with the UK potentially adopting it first, followe